flawed_nl_solution:
Carter can make 6 + 5 + 8 = <<6+5+8=19>>19 cakes regularly for a week.
For this week, he made 6 x 3 = <<6*3=18>>18 cheesecakes.
He made 5 x 3 = <<5*3=51>>51 muffins.
And also made 8 x 3 = <<8*3=24>>24 red velvet cakes.
Carter was able to make 18 + 51 + 24 = <<18+51+24=93>>93 cakes for this week.
Therefore, Carter was able to make 93 - 19 = <<93-19=74>>74 more cakes for this week.
#### 74
